## Hints for Future Agents
- is_latest is HYBRID: explicit "latest" alias row wins; the column flag is
  the fallback (mirrors _IS_LATEST_FROM_ALIASES_SQL and the CH window
  fallback). obj_delete re-points the column to the newest survivor.
- obj_create's version_index counts ALL versions including soft-deleted
  ones, and re-creating a deleted digest resurrects the row in place
  (ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE parity).
- Table rows are content-addressed with first-writer-wins across projects;
  reads filter by project — a second project writing identical content
  cannot read it back. SQLite behaves the same (digest UNIQUE).
- table_query sorts/slices raw entries and only deep-copies the returned
  page — added for performance; keep it that way.

